queues

Class MyTunesTest

  • java.lang.Object
    • queues.MyTunesTest

  • public class MyTunesTest
extends java.lang.Object
    Creates an object of type MyTunes which simulates a playlist queue. Enqueues and dequeues SongEntry objects from each playlist. Simulates playing each song and finally checks the state of each playlist. Simulates testing with large input files Generates large test file tunes4.txt using Math.random() Times amount of time taken
    Author:
    Foothill College, Anuva Banwasi

      • main

        public static void main(java.lang.String[] args)
        Creates one object of type MillionSongSubset class, which reads input from a JSON file. Uses the attributes stored in JSON object to store all entries in an array of SongEntry objects. Next, it parses a plain-text file which lists the names of each playlist. Then queues up songs for each playlist. Simulates playing a requested number of songs. Finally, it reports back if a playlist is empty.
        Parameters:
        args - Not used.
